---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Systems Geek NZ"
  description="Systems Geek NZ provides consultancy, development, and system administration services for small businesses."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow">IT consultancy for small business</div>
        <h1>Practical IT help without the enterprise nonsense.</h1>
        <p>
          Systems Geek NZ is a small IT company focused on helping businesses with
          reliable technology, custom development, and day-to-day systems support.
          We work across consultancy, development, and system administration to keep
          things simple, stable, and effective.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="#contact">Get in touch</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="#services">View services</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stack">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="stat-title">What we do</div>
          <div class="stat-value">Consultancy, development, and sysadmin work</div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="stat-title">Who we help</div>
          <div class="stat-value">Small businesses needing dependable IT support</div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="stat-title">Approach</div>
          <div class="stat-value">Straightforward advice, practical solutions, solid systems</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="about">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">About Systems Geek NZ</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">
        We help small businesses make better use of technology. That might mean
        advising on infrastructure, building internal tools, improving reliability,
        maintaining servers, automating repetitive tasks, or cleaning up systems that
        have become difficult to manage.
      </p>
      <p class="section-copy">
        Our focus is on practical outcomes: systems that are easier to run, software
        that solves real problems, and support that is responsive and clear.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="services">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Services</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">
        We provide a small, focused set of services for businesses that need capable
        technical help without hiring a full internal team.
      </p>

      <div class="services">
        <div class="card service">
          <h3>Consultancy</h3>
          <p>
            Advice on infrastructure, hosting, security, workflows, and technology
            decisions. Ideal for businesses that need experienced guidance before
            making changes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card service">
          <h3>Development</h3>
          <p>
            Custom tools, internal systems, automation, and web-based solutions
            tailored to your business. We build things that are maintainable and
            useful, not overengineered.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card service">
          <h3>System Administration</h3>
          <p>
            Server management, deployments, monitoring, backups, troubleshooting,
            and ongoing technical upkeep to keep business systems stable and secure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card contact-box">
        <div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Get in touch</h2>
          <p>
            Need help with a project, ongoing support, or general technical advice?
            Systems Geek NZ can help with consultancy, development, and system
            administration for your business.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:hello@systems.geek.nz">
            hello@systems.geek.nz
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
